➡️ VLAN Configuration on Router 1 (R1)

configure terminal

interface FastEthernet0/0
 no ip address
 no shutdown
exit

interface FastEthernet0/0.10
 encapsulation dot1Q 10
 ip address 195.120.150.1 255.255.255.224
exit

interface FastEthernet0/0.20
 encapsulation dot1Q 20
 ip address 195.120.150.225 255.255.255.224
exit

end
copy running-config startup-config


Command Explanations:
	•	enable
Enters privileged EXEC mode.
	•	configure terminal
Enters global configuration mode.
	•	interface FastEthernet0/0
Selects the physical interface connected to the switch.
	•	no ip address
Removes IP from physical interface because it will act as a trunk.
	•	no shutdown
Activates the interface.
	•	interface FastEthernet0/0.10
Creates a subinterface for VLAN 10.
	•	encapsulation dot1Q 10
Enables VLAN tagging for VLAN 10.
	•	ip address 195.120.150.1 255.255.255.224
Assigns gateway IP for VLAN 10 network.
	•	interface FastEthernet0/0.20
Creates a subinterface for VLAN 20.
	•	encapsulation dot1Q 20
Enables VLAN tagging for VLAN 20.
	•	ip address 195.120.150.33 255.255.255.224
Assigns gateway IP for VLAN 20 network.
	•	end
Exits configuration mode.
	•	copy running-config startup-config
Saves configuration permanently.


